        "row_Q4wMgN": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"faq-wrapper\">\n<h2>Faqs</h2>\n  <faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">\nWhat is included in the Himalayan Cliff Honey subscription?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">All of our products are available for subscription, just a click and cliff honey from the Himalayas of Nepal gets delivered to your doorstep regularly.\n<br><br>\nYou can choose the number of jars and the variants you want.\n</p>\n  </faq>\n    <faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">\nHow does the subscription work?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">\nOnce you subscribe, your chosen products arrive at your doorstep automatically- in the time period you select. By subscribing, you receive 10% off every single jar each time with autobilling processed before each shipment.</p>\n  </faq>\n    <faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">\nHow do I manage or update my subscription?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">You can change your preferred product or update other subscription details from your account. Edit your preferences, shipping address or payment and manage your subscription anytime by logging into your account. Simple as that.\n</p>\n  </faq>\n    <faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">Is there a discount or benefit for subscribing?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">Yes! Subscribers get 20% off on their first purchase and 10% afterwards, on each repeated purchase. For one-time purchasers, the discount is 10%. As Himalayan cliff honey is harvested only at specific times of the year, subscribing gives you early access to fresh harvests and limited edition batches.\n</p>\n  </faq>\n    <faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">What is your cancellation policy?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">Cancelling is as easy as subscribing. Just unsubscribe from your account and you’re done. For a full refund, make sure to cancel the subscription before the order has been shipped. If the order has already been processed for shipment, it cannot be cancelled, but our team will guide you on return or exchange options.\n</p>\n  </faq>\n<faq>\n    <h4 class=\"question\">\nWhen should I expect my Honey?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">\nYou’ll receive your jar of honey 4 to 7 days after the order date. For confirmation, you will receive an email with tracking once the order has been shipped.\n</p>\n  </faq>\n<faq>\n <h4 class=\"question\">\nWhat are the payment options? \n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">\nWe accept all major credit cards for our subscriptions or you can easily check out through PayPal Express, Apple Pay or Shop Pay. Each order is billed right before it ships!\n</p>\n  </faq>\n<faq>\n <h4 class=\"question\">\nHow can I use dedicated support?\n</h4>\n    <p class=\"answer\">\nShoot us an email at contact@cliffhoney.com or message us at Whatsapp. \n</p>\n  </faq>\n</div>\n{% style %}\n.faq-wrapper {\n  width: 100%;\n}\n\n.faq-wrapper faq {\n  display: block;                 \n  border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor; \n}\n\n.faq-wrapper faq:last-child {\n  border-bottom: 0;\n}\n\n.faq-wrapper .question {\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 18px 0;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  user-select: none;\n}\n\n\n.faq-wrapper .question::after {\n  content: url('data:image/svg+xml,<svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M1 7L12 18L23 7\" stroke=\"%234B5441\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>');\n  transition: transform 200ms ease;\nmargin-left: 18px;\n  flex: 0 0 clamp(12px, 0.94vw,18px);\n}\n\n\n.faq-wrapper .answer {\n  margin: 0;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  max-height: 0;\n  opacity: 0;\n  transition: max-height 260ms ease, opacity 200ms ease;\n  padding: 0; \n}\n\n\n.faq-wrapper faq.is-open .answer {\n  opacity: 1;\n  max-height: 500px;\n  padding: 0 0 18px 0;\n}\n\n.faq-wrapper faq.is-open .question::after {\n  transform: rotate(-180deg); \n}\n\n{% endstyle %}\n<script>\n(() => {\n  const wrappers = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-wrapper');\n  if (!wrappers.length) return;\n\n  wrappers.forEach((wrapper) => {\n    const items = Array.from(wrapper.querySelectorAll('faq'));\n\n    const closeItem = (item) => {\n      item.classList.remove('is-open');\n      const answer = item.querySelector('.answer');\n      if (answer) answer.style.maxHeight = '0px';\n      const q = item.querySelector('.question');\n      if (q) q.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');\n    };\n\n    const openItem = (item) => {\n      item.classList.add('is-open');\n      const answer = item.querySelector('.answer');\n      if (answer) answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';\n      const q = item.querySelector('.question');\n      if (q) q.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');\n    };\n\n    items.forEach((item) => {\n      const q = item.querySelector('.question');\n      const a = item.querySelector('.answer');\n      if (!q || !a) return;\n\n      item.style.display = 'block';\n      a.style.maxHeight = '0px';\n\n      q.setAttribute('role', 'button');\n      q.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');\n      q.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');\n\n      const toggle = () => {\n        const isOpen = item.classList.contains('is-open');\n\n        items.forEach((other) => {\n          if (other !== item) closeItem(other);\n        });\n\n        if (isOpen) closeItem(item);\n        else openItem(item);\n      };\n\n      q.addEventListener('click', toggle);\n      q.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {\n        if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {\n          e.preventDefault();\n          toggle();\n        }\n      });\n    });\n\n    window.addEventListener(\n      'resize',\n      () => {\n        const open = wrapper.querySelector('faq.is-open .answer');\n        if (open) open.style.maxHeight = open.scrollHeight + 'px';\n      },\n      { passive: true }\n    );\n  });\n})();\n</script>",
